The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Bengal | Jhargram bandh
                                                                        Friday , November 13 , 2009                                                                                                                                                                                              Jhargram bandh
          OUR CORRESPONDENT                              
	Midnapore, Nov. 12: All shops and businesses in Jhargram subdivision were shut today, the first day of a 72-hour bandh called by the Peoples Committee Against Police Atrocities.        
	Tribals set ablaze a private pick-up van that had ventured out. No one was injured.         
	The bandh has been called to protest yesterdays police lathicharge in Jhargram.        
	Prohibitory orders have been clamped.         
	The police also arrested six persons today near Bakshi village in connection with a gun battle with Maoists yesterday.         
	The Trinamul Congress and the SUCI have claimed that five of the arrested six are their supporters.         
	Also a Peoples Committee leader claimed that all six were active members of the outfit, said to be backed by the Maoists.                                                                                                                                                                             
